author: Suhas Nayse
title: Nagpur shuttlers disappoint in All India Junior Badminton tournament
text:
NAGPUR: City shuttlers disappointed in the main draw matches of the 24th Krishna Khaitan Memorial All India Junior Ranking Badminton Tournament at Chandigarh on Friday. 

Sourabh Kerhalkar, Gaurav Mithe and Rashi Lamba all lost after doing so well in the qualifying rounds. 

NAGPUR RESULTS 

U-19 boys singles: Sourabh Kerhalkar lost to Orijit Chaliha 22-24, 22-20, 14-21. 

U-19 boys doubles: Sourabh Kerhalkar-Vineet Kamble lost to Tushar Sharma-Harsh Singh 15-21, 24-22, 8-21. 

U-17 boys doubles: 7-Sourabh Kerhalkar-Deep Rambhiya lost to Navaneeth Bakka-Sri Krishna Sai Kumar Podile 18-21, 22-24. 

U-17 boys singles: Gaurav Mithe lost to Alap Mishra 13-21, 19-21. 

U-17 girls singles: Rashi Lambe lost to 2-Kanika Kanwal 20-22, 21-17, 12-21.
